<inglise>Additional data (the name of the ship, size of the crew, number of passengers, cargo, port of departure and need for quarantine) shall be submitted to the Border Guard at least four hours prior to the arrival of the ship. </inglise>
<eesti>Etteteatamata laevade saabumisest sadamasse peab sadama vastutav isik teatama piirivalvele viivitamata ning tagama, et piirivalvetoimkonna saabumiseni laevapere liikmed ja reisijad laevast ei v&auml;ljuks ega keegi kaldalt laevale ei l&auml;heks, et laevalt kaldale ja kaldalt laevale ei toimetataks kaupu v&otilde;i esemeid. </eesti>
<inglise>The responsible person of a port shall promptly notify the Border Guard if a ship arrives in the port without notice and ensure that crew members and passengers do not disembark from the ship, that no-one embarks on the ship from the shore, and that goods or objects are not conveyed ashore from the ship or from the shore to the ship until the arrival of a Border Guard unit. </inglise>
