<eesti>Piirivalve tegevuspiirkonnas on piirivalvel &otilde;igus kontrollida piirire&zcaron;iimi rikkumises kahtlustatava isikut t&otilde;endavaid dokumente ning teostada kohapeal isiku ja tema asjade ning transpordivahendi l&auml;bivaatust. </eesti>
<inglise>The Border Guard has the right, within the territory in which it operates, to check the identity documents of persons suspected to have violated the border regime and to conduct on-the-spot checks of such persons and their personal effects and means of transport. </inglise>
<eesti>48. </eesti>
<inglise>48. </inglise>
<eesti>Piirivalve tegevuspiirkonnas on isikud ja transpordivahendid kohustatud vormiriietuses piirivalveametniku antud m&auml;rguande peale peatuma ning isikud esitama neid peatanud piirivalveametniku n&otilde;udmisel isikut t&otilde;endava dokumendi, samuti dokumendid s&otilde;iduki ja veose kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>Within the territory in which the Border Guard operates, persons and means of transport are required to stop at a signal given by a uniformed Border Guard official, and persons are required to present an identity document and also documentation concerning the vehicle and load at the request of the Border Guard official who stopped the persons. </inglise>
<eesti>49. </eesti>
<inglise>49. </inglise>
<eesti>Piiratud tsiviilk&auml;ibega relvade, laskemoona, l&otilde;hkematerjali ja muude esemete olemasolu korral peab piirivalve tegevuspiirkonnas olev isik esitama piirivalveametniku n&otilde;udmisel nende omamise, kandmise ja kasutamise &otilde;igust kinnitavad dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>If a person within the territory in which the Border Guard operates has weapons, ammunition, explosive substances or other objects in restricted commerce with him or her, the person shall, at the request of a Border Guard official, present documentation certifying the right of the person to own, carry and use such objects. </inglise>
<eesti>50. </eesti>
