<eesti>S&otilde;jalaeva v&otilde;i muu riiklikku &uuml;lesannet t&auml;itva laeva, allveelaeva ja tuumalaeva rahumeelne l&auml;bis&otilde;it territoriaalmerest toimub riigipiiri seaduse (RT I 1994, 54, 902; 1997, 77, 1315) paragrahvis 13 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The innocent passage of warships, other ships performing state functions, submarines and nuclear-powered ships through the territorial sea shall take place pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 13 of the State Borders Act (RT I 1994, 54, 902; 1997, 77, 1315). </inglise>
<eesti>Tuumalaev k&auml;esoleva eeskirja m&otilde;istes on laev, millel on tuumaj&otilde;useade v&otilde;i mille pardal on tuumarelv. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purpose of these Rules, a nuclear-powered ship is a ship with a nuclear engine or a ship carrying a nuclear weapon on board. </inglise>
<eesti>56. </eesti>
<inglise>56. </inglise>
<eesti>Eestisse saabuvatel laevadel enne piiripunkti j&otilde;udmist ja Eestist lahkuvatel laevadel p&auml;rast piirikontrolli l&auml;bimist, samuti territoriaalmerest rahumeelset l&auml;bis&otilde;itu teostavatel ja tormivarjus seisvatel laevadel on keelatud astuda niisugusesse otsesesse kontakti teiste laevadega, mis v&otilde;imaldaks inimeste, kauba ja esemete laevalt laevale &uuml;leandmist. </eesti>
<inglise>It is prohibited for ships arriving in Estonia, prior to their arrival at a border checkpoint, ships departing from Estonia, after undergoing border controls, ships conducting innocent passage through the territorial sea and ships sheltering from a storm to have direct contact with other ships which would enable persons, goods or objects to be transferred from one ship to another. </inglise>
<eesti>57. </eesti>
<inglise>57. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva eeskirja punktis 59 nimetatud laevadel on keelatud isikute laevast v&auml;ljumine ja laevale asumine, samuti kaupade peale-, maha- ja &uuml;mberlaadimine ning vedurlaevadel j&auml;relveetavate praamide vahetamine ilma piirivalve eelneva loata. </eesti>
<inglise>The disembarkation of persons from ships specified in clause 59 of these Rules, the embarkation of persons on such ships, the loading, unloading and reloading of goods and the changing of lighters towed by a tug is prohibited without the prior permission of the Border Guard. </inglise>
<eesti>Loetletud toimingute sooritamine avariiolukordades v&otilde;i &otilde;nnetusjuhtumite korral tuleb koosk&otilde;lastada piirivalvega. </eesti>
<inglise>Approval shall be obtained from the Border Guard for the performance of such activities in emergency situations or in the case of an accident. </inglise>
